column2: To heat: Place the croissants on a baking tray and heat in a preheated oven (180°C, gas mark 4) for 5 minutes.
Preheat the oven to 200C for 30 mins or until it comes up to temperature.
Bake in the oven at 230°C, for an average of 17 minutes and adding steam.
To heat: Place the croissants on a baking tray and heat in a preheated oven (180°C, gas mark 4) for 5 minutes.
Bake in the preheated oven at 190C (fan oven on) for 6 minutes, then lower the temperature to 170C for another 10 minutes.
Preheat the oven at 200 C/ 392 F.

Roll
up the croissants, let rise for 2 hours at 24-25°C, Brush on egg
wash and bake for about 20 mn in a convection oven at 170°C.
